10:06 Defendant Brennan W Jackson in court with attorney Travis Stephen Slattery.  Kelly A. Lehn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Jordan Jazdzewski is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Lehn. He is a police officer with the Wisconsin Rapids Police Department. On 6/24/14, he spoke with B.D.H., a 12-year-old female. He states that she was at a residence in the City of Wisconsin Rapids and the defendant touched her inappropriately. He spoke to defendant regarding allegations. He admitted to touching B.D.H. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom. Attorney Slattery cross-examines witness. 
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Bond is continued.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for August 8, 2014 at 10:00 am.
